main event: Several objects observed moving from NW to SE, disappearing after approximately two minutes of observation.
interesting points: The sighting was recorded on December 6, 1959,, The objects were first tracked by Ground Radar,, The sighting occurred 95 miles SE of Point Tuna, Bahamas,, There is speculation that the sighting may have been related to a satellite launched from Cape Canaveral,, The conclusion included possibilities such as a balloon or astronomical phenomenon, but deemed insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Military source; no individual witnesses mentioned
